1
00:01:26,770 --> 00:01:30,770
=My Dear Guardian=

2
00:01:31,340 --> 00:01:34,120
=Episode 27=

3
00:01:38,660 --> 00:01:43,600
♪In my sadness, I hallucinate♪

4
00:01:45,080 --> 00:01:50,380
♪Let it be, I'm once again
close to tears♪

5
00:01:51,150 --> 00:01:56,840
♪An unfamiliar street,
a cruel heartbeat♪

6
00:01:57,040 --> 00:02:03,699
♪Time stops, tears are meaningless
in this moment♪

7
00:02:04,270 --> 00:02:07,510
♪All I want is a hug♪

8
00:02:07,830 --> 00:02:10,790
♪Dr.unk on your lips♪

9
00:02:11,010 --> 00:02:16,900
♪It's the trickery played by hormones♪

10
00:02:17,470 --> 00:02:19,730
His spine is a little crooked.

11
00:02:23,350 --> 00:02:27,170
When he carried me down
the stairs yesterday, I felt it.

12
00:02:28,020 --> 00:02:29,250
To be frank,

13
00:02:29,780 --> 00:02:31,480
after I turned 14,

14
00:02:31,980 --> 00:02:33,850
I haven't seen much of him.

15
00:02:35,990 --> 00:02:37,810
It's highly unlikely that I had caused...

16
00:02:39,270 --> 00:02:41,320
his back to be crooked.

17
00:02:42,070 --> 00:02:43,730
In my memory,

18
00:02:44,220 --> 00:02:48,430
I remember how he would carry me
on his shoulders when I was a kid,

19
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:51,540
and held me high up.

20
00:02:54,150 --> 00:02:55,210
Now,

21
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:57,840
how did his spine become crooked?

22
00:03:01,010 --> 00:03:02,660
Perhaps it's lack of calcium.

23
00:03:05,230 --> 00:03:07,280
I know about those scientific theories.

24
00:03:08,710 --> 00:03:10,410
What I wish to say is,

25
00:03:10,910 --> 00:03:12,329
just because this man...

26
00:03:13,710 --> 00:03:15,370
wears a police uniform,

27
00:03:16,940 --> 00:03:19,890
I believed that he was invincible.

28
00:03:21,710 --> 00:03:24,890
Who knew he'd get exhausted too?

29
00:03:26,240 --> 00:03:27,970
Maybe other people don't see it.

30
00:03:28,060 --> 00:03:29,680
He himself doesn't see it.

31
00:03:30,450 --> 00:03:32,150
But I can.

32
00:03:34,100 --> 00:03:35,760
His back is crooked.

33
00:03:44,100 --> 00:03:46,200
I'm heartbroken.

34
00:03:50,057 --> 00:03:51,630
Just like you said,

35
00:03:53,530 --> 00:03:55,310
I still hate him.

36
00:03:56,290 --> 00:03:58,670
Still, I wish I could do
something for him.

37
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:02,650
But I'm just a lunatic.

38
00:04:04,270 --> 00:04:05,400
You're not.

39
00:04:08,340 --> 00:04:10,370
You know what I said to him yesterday?

40
00:04:11,029 --> 00:04:12,019
I said,

41
00:04:12,190 --> 00:04:13,760
"Stay away from me."

42
00:04:14,190 --> 00:04:16,089
"I hate you."

43
00:04:27,390 --> 00:04:29,890
If he doesn't wake up,

44
00:04:31,659 --> 00:04:33,970
that would be the last thing...

45
00:04:34,430 --> 00:04:36,320
I ever said to him.

46
00:04:39,110 --> 00:04:40,480
That would be...

47
00:04:41,820 --> 00:04:44,080
our farewell.

48
00:04:56,740 --> 00:04:58,890
Perhaps this is a hint from God.

49
00:05:00,990 --> 00:05:02,090
Only that...

50
00:05:03,270 --> 00:05:05,170
it was done in a more dangerous way.

51
00:05:07,590 --> 00:05:08,810
Right.

52
00:05:09,250 --> 00:05:11,030
This is a huge hint.

53
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:18,540
Blood connection
is stronger than you think.

54
00:05:19,300 --> 00:05:20,280
Xiao Xue.

55
00:05:21,540 --> 00:05:24,250
Just because he doesn't convey
his emotions wilfully like you,

56
00:05:24,550 --> 00:05:26,010
doesn't mean he doesn't care.

57
00:05:31,940 --> 00:05:34,290
Daddy, I feel sick.

58
00:05:34,450 --> 00:05:36,110
I want to go home.

59
00:05:36,835 --> 00:05:38,315
I'll take you home
once you finish the Dr.ip.

60
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:39,260
Be good.

61
00:05:39,350 --> 00:05:40,460
Please.

62
00:05:40,580 --> 00:05:42,260
I want to go home now.

63
00:05:42,390 --> 00:05:43,690
Be good, Tian Tian.

64
00:05:44,298 --> 00:05:47,250
I'll buy you delicious snacks
when you finish the Dr.ip, okay?

65
00:05:47,650 --> 00:05:49,630
You mean it, right?

66
00:05:49,710 --> 00:05:52,852
Promise me you'll stay with me too.
You mustn't leave.

67
00:05:53,030 --> 00:05:55,978
I promise you, I'll stay by your side.

68
00:05:56,063 --> 00:05:58,250
Okay. Pinky promise.

69
00:05:59,220 --> 00:06:03,460
Pinky promise binds you
to the word for 100 years.

70
00:06:03,550 --> 00:06:05,370
If you break it, you'll become a dog.

71
00:06:05,990 --> 00:06:07,090
Good girl.

72
00:06:12,770 --> 00:06:14,070
Do you have pen and paper?

73
00:06:14,630 --> 00:06:15,610
I'll get some.

74
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:37,020
What's this?

75
00:07:41,159 --> 00:07:43,120
I modified it using
the unit's bulletproof vest.

76
00:07:44,070 --> 00:07:45,660
I use it when I'm Dr.essed
in civilian clothing.

77
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:47,330
I want you to have it.

78
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:50,020
What for?

79
00:07:50,580 --> 00:07:51,880
To keep you safe.

80
00:07:52,470 --> 00:07:53,940
I'm wearing a bra.

81
00:07:54,030 --> 00:07:55,450
How am I supposed to wear this?

82
00:08:01,230 --> 00:08:03,380
Maybe go back and try to...

83
00:08:04,530 --> 00:08:06,390
Try to find a way.

84
00:08:07,750 --> 00:08:09,060
Such a straight guy.

85
00:08:09,150 --> 00:08:12,890
Put away the heart protector.
I don't want to catch sight of it.

86
00:08:13,190 --> 00:08:14,370
Why?

87
00:08:14,580 --> 00:08:15,790
It's ugly.

88
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:19,100
Isn't is obvious?
I don't want to see it.

89
00:08:23,980 --> 00:08:25,210
Is it ugly?

90
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,020
You still donated blood
despite your injury?

91
00:08:41,700 --> 00:08:43,850
Worry about yourself first, Dr.. Xia.

92
00:08:43,940 --> 00:08:45,210
I'm doing good.

93
00:08:45,300 --> 00:08:46,170
Good?

94
00:08:46,270 --> 00:08:47,990
That parcel was sent to you.

95
00:08:48,070 --> 00:08:50,490
If you got blown up by it,
would you still be good?

96
00:08:52,850 --> 00:08:54,110
Were you worried about me?

97
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:55,420
Of course.

98
00:09:01,390 --> 00:09:02,860
Who was the sender?

99
00:09:02,950 --> 00:09:04,290
The police is still investigating.

100
00:09:21,630 --> 00:09:22,550
My coffee.

101
00:09:22,630 --> 00:09:24,530
Don't move. Come here.

102
00:09:25,570 --> 00:09:26,590
What are you doing?

103
00:09:27,870 --> 00:09:28,770
What are you doing? Hey.

104
00:09:28,950 --> 00:09:29,850
Sit down.

105
00:09:34,130 --> 00:09:34,980
Relax.

106
00:09:35,060 --> 00:09:35,940
Relax.

107
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:37,740
Relax.

108
00:09:44,820 --> 00:09:46,600
Enjoy this moment.

109
00:09:58,270 --> 00:09:59,330
How is it?

110
00:10:00,180 --> 00:10:01,560
Left. The left side.

111
00:10:03,290 --> 00:10:04,790
Yes, that's the spot.

112
00:10:13,860 --> 00:10:14,960
Liang Mu Ze.

113
00:10:16,550 --> 00:10:20,310
With your skills,
you'll be able to run a massage shop.

114
00:10:20,390 --> 00:10:22,250
I'm sure you'll have returning customers.

115
00:10:23,340 --> 00:10:25,970
This is my family's ancestral skill.

116
00:10:27,180 --> 00:10:28,280
However,

117
00:10:28,630 --> 00:10:30,100
this skill of ours...

118
00:10:30,950 --> 00:10:33,730
is reserved
for only one person this whole life.

119
00:10:41,670 --> 00:10:42,660
Xia Chu.

120
00:10:43,990 --> 00:10:45,290
Do think it over again.

121
00:10:45,790 --> 00:10:47,130
Come to the unit.

122
00:10:48,750 --> 00:10:49,730
Where?

123
00:10:51,140 --> 00:10:57,400
♪Every minute, every second,
how do I resist?♪

124
00:10:58,060 --> 00:11:04,650
♪I can't help but look forward
to your return♪

125
00:11:05,620 --> 00:11:06,530
See?

126
00:11:06,870 --> 00:11:09,010
We don't have answers to many questions.

127
00:11:11,750 --> 00:11:14,650
But there's one answer
that I'm sure of.

128
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:17,980
What is it?

129
00:11:22,070 --> 00:11:24,880
The moon is lovely tonight.

130
00:11:34,780 --> 00:11:35,660
Yes, it is.

131
00:11:36,820 --> 00:11:38,620
Alright, Captain Liang.
Thank you.

132
00:11:38,710 --> 00:11:40,210
I feel rejuvenated now.

133
00:11:40,470 --> 00:11:41,890
I can return to my work.

134
00:11:42,890 --> 00:11:44,790
Hope your hand recovers well.

135
00:11:47,250 --> 00:11:48,790
Do you still remember the tips...

136
00:11:49,670 --> 00:11:51,480
I taught you about staying safe?

137
00:11:54,020 --> 00:11:56,810
Don't travel alone.
Do not stay in the hotel alone.

138
00:11:56,900 --> 00:11:59,100
Set the speed dial
to call the police.

139
00:11:59,190 --> 00:12:01,080
Shut the doors and windows
when alone at home.

140
00:12:01,190 --> 00:12:02,820
Do not put down the home adDr.ess
for deliveries.

141
00:12:02,910 --> 00:12:05,290
Take note of the location
of lifts, stairs and alarms.

142
00:12:05,390 --> 00:12:07,770
Aside from that,
no matter how fast a lift goes,

143
00:12:07,870 --> 00:12:10,940
a person running can catch up
to it within three floors.

144
00:12:11,030 --> 00:12:13,380
So during emergencies,
in order to ditch pursuers,

145
00:12:13,470 --> 00:12:15,510
choose to go further than three floors.

146
00:12:15,590 --> 00:12:18,030
Press more floors if needed
to confuse the pursuer.

147
00:12:18,130 --> 00:12:20,540
Anything around me
can be used as a makeshift weapon.

148
00:12:20,630 --> 00:12:21,980
If I really can't get away,

149
00:12:22,070 --> 00:12:24,960
then go to somewhere with people
and call for help.

150
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:26,760
Captain Liang.

151
00:12:27,430 --> 00:12:28,500
What you've told me,

152
00:12:28,790 --> 00:12:30,680
I have them etched in my mind.

153
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:32,300
I won't forget it.

154
00:12:33,810 --> 00:12:34,910
Not bad.

155
00:12:36,510 --> 00:12:37,450
I'm off.

156
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:54,290
-Dr. Zhang.
-Doctor.

157
00:12:54,380 --> 00:12:55,410
Why are you here?

158
00:12:55,505 --> 00:12:57,075
This is Ke Wei's grandmother.

159
00:12:57,160 --> 00:12:58,435
We just came
from the Public Security Bureau.

160
00:12:58,520 --> 00:12:59,840
We were told Ke Wei was sent here.

161
00:12:59,930 --> 00:13:01,190
How is he?

162
00:13:01,550 --> 00:13:02,450
Doctor.

163
00:13:02,950 --> 00:13:04,170
He's badly injured.

164
00:13:05,340 --> 00:13:06,710
What's most life-threatening is that...

165
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:10,790
the foreign object pierced through
the right atrium penetrating the heart,

166
00:13:10,880 --> 00:13:13,565
and right chest,
straight up the right side of the neck.

167
00:13:14,010 --> 00:13:15,040
In addition,

168
00:13:15,220 --> 00:13:18,360
the cut in the right atrium
is very close to the coronary artery.

169
00:13:18,510 --> 00:13:21,280
We haven't been able to determine
if the aorta is damaged.

170
00:13:21,580 --> 00:13:24,340
We can only find out during the operation.

171
00:13:24,790 --> 00:13:27,010
Doctor, please, I'm begging you.

172
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:29,580
You have to save him.

173
00:13:29,710 --> 00:13:33,245
He is the only heir of the family.

174
00:13:33,640 --> 00:13:34,520
Madam.

175
00:13:34,690 --> 00:13:35,970
Please calm down.

176
00:13:36,060 --> 00:13:37,050
Tell me.

177
00:13:37,160 --> 00:13:40,400
Does he have any criminal record
or history of mental illness?

178
00:13:40,830 --> 00:13:42,090
No, none.

179
00:13:42,170 --> 00:13:44,480
My grandson has always been good.

180
00:13:44,590 --> 00:13:46,090
He's a good kid.

181
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:49,810
Doctor, this man is very important
in our following investigation.

182
00:13:49,920 --> 00:13:52,500
Please do your best to save him.

183
00:13:52,660 --> 00:13:53,500
Don't worry.

184
00:13:53,590 --> 00:13:55,220
As a doctor,
we'll do everything in our power.

185
00:13:55,300 --> 00:13:57,810
-Thank you.
-If there are no problems,

186
00:13:58,070 --> 00:13:59,570
please sign this consent form.

187
00:14:09,820 --> 00:14:11,730
I can't believe you agreed
to do the operation.

188
00:14:12,290 --> 00:14:13,160
What to do.

189
00:14:13,250 --> 00:14:14,360
Director Chen is overseas.

190
00:14:14,510 --> 00:14:15,730
Dr. Lu is sick.

191
00:14:15,815 --> 00:14:18,260
I'm the only one with experience
treating foreign matter penetration.

192
00:14:18,350 --> 00:14:19,530
Who else is going to do it?

193
00:14:19,610 --> 00:14:21,160
He blew up several people today.

194
00:14:21,310 --> 00:14:24,290
That's why we need to save him,
so that he can be interrogated.

195
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:27,900
Putting aside his injuries,
the incident today is a huge deal.

196
00:14:27,980 --> 00:14:30,060
Have you considered the risks
of saving him?

197
00:14:30,150 --> 00:14:31,490
The police will be monitoring.

198
00:14:31,630 --> 00:14:33,890
Our media department
will be recording the whole process.

199
00:14:34,950 --> 00:14:35,830
Besides,

200
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:37,990
if something did happen,
I could only blame it on bad luck.

201
00:14:38,090 --> 00:14:39,330
You can just ignore it.

202
00:14:39,460 --> 00:14:41,090
You should at least wait for the results,

203
00:14:41,170 --> 00:14:43,710
to his infectious diseases check
before performing the operation.

204
00:14:43,950 --> 00:14:45,180
There's no time.

205
00:14:45,310 --> 00:14:47,170
He may die at any moment.

206
00:14:47,550 --> 00:14:49,410
Don't worry. I'll be careful.

207
00:14:51,210 --> 00:14:52,180
You're unbelievable.

208
00:14:52,270 --> 00:14:53,660
You always think you're right.

209
00:14:53,750 --> 00:14:55,970
Be it at work or in relationships.

210
00:14:56,220 --> 00:14:59,080
You and Chen Meng Zhen
are not compatible at all.

211
00:15:00,910 --> 00:15:02,370
You and I are compatible.

212
00:15:02,560 --> 00:15:04,250
We're both smart and cautious.

213
00:15:04,340 --> 00:15:05,440
How did that end up?

214
00:15:06,370 --> 00:15:08,720
Dr. Zhang, the patient's blood pressure
is falling.

215
00:15:15,620 --> 00:15:16,580
What's the situation?

216
00:15:16,670 --> 00:15:17,890
He's spazzing non-stop.

217
00:15:18,910 --> 00:15:20,710
-Begin anaesthesia.
-Okay.

218
00:15:20,870 --> 00:15:23,690
Ke Wei, it doesn't matter
what happened before.

219
00:15:23,790 --> 00:15:25,620
Right now, you're my patient.

220
00:15:25,710 --> 00:15:27,310
I'm trying to save you.

221
00:15:27,390 --> 00:15:28,630
I hope to get your cooperation.

222
00:15:28,710 --> 00:15:31,410
At least, let your family
see you again, all right?

223
00:15:32,560 --> 00:15:33,470
Ready to open the chest.

224
00:15:46,100 --> 00:15:47,250
Steady.

225
00:15:47,710 --> 00:15:48,820
Let's finish it in one go.

226
00:15:48,910 --> 00:15:49,990
Ready.

227
00:15:50,080 --> 00:15:51,540
One, two.

228
00:15:54,730 --> 00:15:56,770
Apply pressure.
Use the hemostatic forceps.

229
00:15:57,700 --> 00:15:59,040
Over here.

230
00:16:01,350 --> 00:16:02,410
Sorry, sir.

231
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:04,290
It's okay.
Stop the bleeding with gauze.

232
00:16:07,890 --> 00:16:08,950
I'm going to change my gloves.

233
00:16:09,040 --> 00:16:09,920
Okay.

234
00:16:14,100 --> 00:16:15,560
The blood pressure continues to drop.

235
00:16:17,930 --> 00:16:19,270
The pulmonary artery is badly damaged.

236
00:16:19,590 --> 00:16:21,610
Quick, hasten the blood transfusion.

237
00:16:22,590 --> 00:16:23,890
Increase noradrenaline. Quickly!

238
00:16:28,950 --> 00:16:30,050
Move it!

239
00:16:38,510 --> 00:16:40,570
(In operation)

240
00:16:44,500 --> 00:16:46,200
Doctor...

241
00:16:46,280 --> 00:16:47,940
How is my grandson?

242
00:16:49,660 --> 00:16:51,880
Say... Say something.

243
00:16:52,430 --> 00:16:54,290
Say something.

244
00:17:02,540 --> 00:17:03,880
I'm sorry.

245
00:17:17,190 --> 00:17:18,770
It will be okay.

246
00:17:20,010 --> 00:17:21,440
My grandson.

247
00:17:24,310 --> 00:17:25,260
Mi Gu.

248
00:17:25,940 --> 00:17:26,920
Xia Chu.

249
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:28,260
I've been looking for you.

250
00:17:29,910 --> 00:17:33,240
Wait for me at the ER night shift room.
I'll be right there.

251
00:17:41,190 --> 00:17:43,610
This sentence lacks punch.

252
00:17:43,730 --> 00:17:46,350
But I can't come up
with a better expression.

253
00:17:49,390 --> 00:17:50,410
Highlight it.

254
00:17:50,520 --> 00:17:52,180
We'll go over it again during editing.

255
00:17:52,830 --> 00:17:53,810
Okay.

256
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:57,890
This is everything.

257
00:17:59,750 --> 00:18:01,050
I'll take a copy with me.

258
00:18:07,310 --> 00:18:08,370
Xiao Xiao.

259
00:18:09,550 --> 00:18:12,800
Have you ever thought about
changing your job?

260
00:18:15,560 --> 00:18:16,490
Why do you ask?

261
00:18:17,110 --> 00:18:18,410
Just curious.

262
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:21,540
Say for instance,

263
00:18:22,090 --> 00:18:25,390
you're dating a very busy man
who is abroad.

264
00:18:25,570 --> 00:18:27,060
You two love each other.

265
00:18:27,410 --> 00:18:29,890
Are you willing to change your job
for the sake of your future...

266
00:18:29,970 --> 00:18:31,430
and move to be with him?

267
00:18:32,210 --> 00:18:33,750
Why am I the one to switch jobs?

268
00:18:34,100 --> 00:18:34,980
Why can't he?

269
00:18:37,090 --> 00:18:39,120
His profession is a little special.

270
00:18:39,260 --> 00:18:41,850
It's not up to him
to decide whether he can leave.

271
00:18:43,510 --> 00:18:44,890
You're talking about Liang Mu Ze, right?

272
00:18:46,820 --> 00:18:48,190
It doesn't matter who it is.

273
00:18:48,450 --> 00:18:51,260
I just want to know,
if you were in their shoes...

274
00:18:51,350 --> 00:18:52,230
I won't.

